# CipherChat — QR-Based Chat System with Cyber Attack Simulation

A dark-themed, cybersecurity-inspired chat application that simulates real-time
packet sniffing, DDoS attacks, session hijacking, and geolocation tracking —
all safely inside the browser and a local Python server. No real hacking,
no real network access.

---

## Project Structure

```
cipherchat/
├── app.py            ← Python Flask backend (API + serves the HTML)
├── index.html        ← Frontend UI (HTML + CSS + JavaScript)
├── requirements.txt  ← Python package dependencies
└── README.md         ← This file
```

---

## How It Works

```
Browser (index.html)
       │
       │  REST API calls (fetch)
       ▼
Flask backend (app.py)
  ├── /api/join                → generates username, JWT token, session ID
  ├── /api/room/<id>/metrics   → simulates DDoS, server load, sniffer stats
  ├── /api/room/<id>/messages  → stores and serves chat messages
  ├── /api/room/<id>/bot-message → generates a random bot message
  ├── /api/session/<id>/check  → simulates session attack / token rotation
  ├── /api/geo/rotate          → returns a random attacker geolocation
  └── /api/status              → server health / uptime
```

All backend state is **in-memory** — it resets when you restart `app.py`.
This is intentional for a demo/simulation project.

