## API Reference

All endpoints return JSON `{ "ok": true, ... }`.

| Method | Endpoint | Body / Params | Description |
|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/join` | `{ room_id }` | Join/create room, get token |
| GET  | `/api/room/<id>/metrics` | — | Live dashboard metrics |
| GET  | `/api/room/<id>/messages` | — | Last 100 messages |
| POST | `/api/room/<id>/messages` | `{ session_id, content }` | Send a message |
| POST | `/api/room/<id>/bot-message` | — | Generate a bot message |
| GET  | `/api/session/<id>/check` | — | Session security check |
| GET  | `/api/geo/rotate` | — | Random attacker geolocation |
| GET  | `/api/status` | — | Server health / uptime |

---

## Requirements

- Python 3.9+
- A modern browser (Chrome, Firefox, Edge, Safari)
- Camera permission (optional — only needed for QR scanning)

---

## Notes

- No database is used. All data lives in Python dictionaries for the
  lifetime of the server process.
- No real cryptography, network sniffing, or external connections are
  made. Everything is a safe simulation.
- The frontend loads two CDN resources: the `html5-qrcode` library and
  Google Fonts. Everything else is self-contained.
